  "questionSection": {
    "position": 15,
    "heading": ["Frequently asked", "Questions"],
    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What is MCA (Master of Computer Applications)?",
        "answer": "MCA is a postgraduate program in Computer Applications that focuses on advanced programming, software development, databases, networking, cloud technologies, and emerging IT skills required for modern tech careers."
      },
      {
        "question": "Who is eligible to join the MCA program?",
        "answer": "Students with a BCA, BSc (CS/IT), BTech, or any degree with Mathematics/Computer Science can pursue MCA. Some universities also offer bridge courses for non-IT graduates."
      },
      {
        "question": "How long is the MCA course?",
        "answer": "The duration of MCA is typically 2 years (4 semesters), including theory classes, practical labs, mini-projects, and a final-year industry project."
      },
      {
        "question": "What career opportunities are available after MCA?",
        "answer": "MCA graduates can work as Software Developers, Web Developers, Data Analysts, Database Administrators, Cloud Engineers, Cybersecurity Analysts, System Administrators, AI/ML Engineers, and more in top IT companies."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the average salary after completing MCA?",
        "answer": "Fresh MCA graduates usually earn ₹3–7 LPA, while experienced professionals can earn ₹8–20 LPA+, depending on their skills and chosen specialization."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can working professionals pursue MCA?",
        "answer": "Yes. Many universities provide online, part-time, and weekend MCA programs, making it flexible for working professionals to upskill while continuing their job."
      },
      {
        "question": "What specializations are available in MCA?",
        "answer": "Popular MCA specializations include AI & ML, Data Science, Cloud Computing, Cybersecurity, Blockchain, AR/VR, Full Stack Development, IoT, and Software Engineering."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the scope of MCA in today’s tech industry?",
        "answer": "The demand for skilled IT professionals continues to rise globally. MCA graduates can work in IT services, product-based companies, startups, fintech, cloud industries, cybersecurity firms, and R&D departments with excellent growth potential."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do MCA programs include practical learning and real-time projects?",
        "answer": "Yes. MCA includes labs, coding assignments, internships, capstone projects, and industry tools that prepare students for real-world IT roles."
      },
      {
        "question": "What industries hire MCA graduates?",
        "answer": "MCA graduates are hired across IT services, software development, e-commerce, fintech, banking, healthcare IT, telecom, consulting, and cloud-based product companies."
      }
    ]
  },

